    "desc": "Official site, includes news, biography, galleries, CDs, DVDs, an interview and tour dates.",
    "text": "play\nprevious\nnext\nNOW PLAYING: FEARLESS BLUES\nALBUM: UNCONDITIONAL\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nHOME\nNEWS\nTOUR\nMUSIC\nBIO\nPHOTO/VIDEO\nSTORE\nPRESSKIT\nINFO\nANA'S PICK OF THE WEEK\nNOVEMBER 01, 2022\nTURN MY LUCK\nWHAT'S NEW\nNOVEMBER 01, 2022\nTURN MY LUCK\nCheck out the brand new music-video 'TURN MY LUCK' by SUCCULENT SOUNDS presented by Ana Popovic! Succulent Sounds is an American indie soul band led by guitar-player/songwriter Ana Popovic and bassist/co-producer Buthel, best described as a 'Gumbo of sounds and perspective. Soul, gospel, rock and R&B extravaganza.’\n  Follow Succulent Sounds on Social:\nInsta: instagram.com/succulentsoundsmusic\nFb: facebook.com/SucculentSoundsMusic\nMAY 26, 2022\nLIVING BLUES AWARDS\nAna is a nominee in this year's Living Blues Awards. She is nominated for Blues Artist of the Year (Female). Anyone can vote!\nMAY 13, 2022\nHOMECOMING MAY 22 '22\nBELGRADE!! Homecoming Sunday May 22, 2022 🥰. It has been a few years (Covid 👎) so hope to see you all at Barutana (open-air).Get your tickets via cooltix.rs.\nUPCOMING SHOWS\nDATE / LOCATION\nDec 09 SALVAGE STATION ASHEVILLE, NC, USA\nDec 10 THE BLUE NOTE DURHAM, NC, USA\nDec 11 TIN PAN RICHMOND, USA\nDec 14 PEARL STREET LIVE WASHINGTON, DC, USA\nDec 15 SELLERSVILLE THEATER SELLERSVILLE, PA, USA\nView more tour dates\nHIGHLIGHTS\n2020 marks Ana's 20th Anniversary as a touring musician.\nAna on the cover! Vintage Guitar (US), GuitarPlayer's Gear Guide (US), Blues Music Magazine, (US) Blues Magazine (FR), American Blues Scene (US), Guitar Coach (US), Twoj Blues (Poland), Blues Blast (US) and many more...\nPart of the 'all-star' Experience Hendrix '14 - '19 lineup; a nationwide tour celebrating the music and legacy of Jimi Hendrix. w/ Buddy Guy, Zakk Wylde, Jonny Lang, Kenny Wayne Shepherd and Eric Johnson.\nMusic-video ‘Lasting Kind Of Love ft. Keb’Mo’ exclusive premiere via GRAMMY.com\n\nCan You Stand the Heat as well as Unconditional 'Pick of the week' by USA today\nFeatured artist on NPR Music - NPR programming reaches 26 million listeners every week\n8 x Blues Music Award nominee.\n- Best New Artist Debut ('03)\n- Contemporary Blues Female Artist ('12 '14 '16)\n- Contemporary Blues Album ('12)\n- DVD Of The Year ('12)\n- Blues Rock Artist ('21 '22) \n'Like It On Top', 'Trilogy', 'Can You Stand the Heat' as well as 'Unconditional' in the top 5 of US Best Selling Blues Albums, The Billboard chart\n'Like It On Top' opens at #2 Amazon's top selling Blues Albums\nTop 15 Guitar World's top Blues and Roots Rock Albums.\nhome\nnews\ntour\nmusic\nbio\nphoto/video\nstore\npresskit\ninfo\n© anapopovic.com",
